# Demo-First Development

## Judge Psychology
- Judges see 20+ demos. Yours needs to grab attention in 30 seconds.
- Lead with the WOW moment, not the architecture explanation.
- Have a compelling one-liner: "It's like [known thing] but [differentiator]."
- Show, don't tell. Live demos > slides > descriptions.

## Demo Checklist
- [ ] Works offline / has fallback if API is slow
- [ ] Has pre-loaded example data for instant demo
- [ ] UI is polished enough to not distract from the idea
- [ ] Can explain the idea in one sentence
- [ ] Has a clear "before vs after" narrative
- [ ] Records a backup video in case live demo fails

## Technical Demo Tips
- Add loading states and animations — they buy time and look polished.
- Use WebSockets or SSE for real-time streaming effects.
- Have a "reset demo" button/script for quick restarts.
- Keep terminal output clean during demos (use logging levels).
